org.jsimpledb.annotation

Annotation Type JSetField


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
@Documented
public @interface JSetField
    Java annotation for the getter methods of Java bean properties reflecting JLayer Set fields.

    The annotated method's return type must be either Set<E>, SortedSet<E>, or NavigableSet<E>, where E is a supported simple type.

    Note that both primitive types and their corresponding wrapper types are supported as elements. A set whose elements have primitive type will throw an exception on an attempt to add a null value. To specify a primitive element type, specify the type name (e.g., "int") as the JField.type() in the element().

        public abstract int storageId

      • element

        public abstract JField element
        Storage ID and index setting for the field's elements. Note: the name property must be left unset.

      • name

        public abstract String name
        The name of this field.

        If empty string (default value), the name is inferred from the name of the annotated Java bean getter method.

        Default:
        ""
